all_base <- read_csv('All_Academics.csv')
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   X1 = col_double(),
##   Sex = col_character(),
##   Basic_Class = col_character(),
##   Rank = col_character(),
##   Admin = col_double(),
##   Subfield = col_character(),
##   Salary_Index = col_double(),
##   SI_Cat = col_character()
## )
all2 <- all_base[-c(1,2,7)]
factor_cols <- c('Basic_Class','Rank','Admin','Subfield','SI_Cat')
all2[factor_cols] <- lapply(all2[factor_cols],factor)
all2$SI_Cat <- factor(all2$SI_Cat, levels=c('One','Two','Three','Four'))
par(omi=c(.5,2,.5,2))
set.seed(123)
decision_tree <- train(SI_Cat ~. , data=all2,method='rpart',trControl=trainControl(method='cv'))
DT2 <- rpart(SI_Cat ~., data=all2)

split.fun <- function(x, labs, digits, varlen, faclen)
{
# replace commas with slashes (needed for strwrap)
labs <- gsub(",", ", ", labs)
for(i in 1:length(labs)) {
# split labs[i] into multiple lines
labs[i] <- paste(strwrap(labs[i], width = 12), collapse = "\n")
}
labs
}


rpart.plot(DT2, box.palette=0, type=5, uniform=TRUE,extra=0,compress=TRUE, ycompress=TRUE, faclen=0, split.fun=split.fun, fallen.leaves=TRUE)

dev.off()

Figure 04

base <- read_excel('ANTH salary data 6_EYC.xlsx',sheet='All Anthros updated')
all <- base[,c(3,5,7,8,11,16)]  # select variables: Sex, Basic Classification, Position Rank, Administrative Duties, Specialty Simple, Salary Index
colnames(all) <- c('Sex','Basic_Class','Rank','Admin','Subfield','Salary_Index')  # rename columns

all$Admin[is.na(all$Admin)] <- 0
factor_cols <- c('Sex','Basic_Class','Rank','Admin','Subfield')  # identify categorical variables
all[factor_cols] <- lapply(all[factor_cols],factor)  # factor categorical variables
all$Basic_Class <- factor(all$Basic_Class, levels=c("Special Focus Four-Year","Associate's Colleges","Baccalaureate College","Master's Colleges & Universities","Doctoral Universities"))
all$Rank <- recode(all$Rank,'Adjunct'='Term','Assistant Professor'='Assistant Professor','Associate Dean and Professor'='Special Rank','Associate Professor'='Associate Professor','Associate Professor and Chair'='Associate Professor','Dean'='Special Rank','Department Head'='Special Rank','Director'='Special Rank','Distinguished Professor'='Special Rank','Distinguished Professor of Science'='Special Rank','Distinguished University Professor'='Special Rank','Instructor'='Term','Lecturer'='Term','PostDoc'='Term','President'='Special Rank','Presidents Professor'='Special Rank','President Emeritus'='Special Rank','Professor'='Full Professor','Professor and Associate Chair'='Full Professor','Provost'='Special Rank','Regents Professor'='Special Rank','VAP'='Term','Vice Provost'='Special Rank')  # Special Rank == Dean, Associate Dean, President, etc
all$Rank <- factor(all$Rank, levels=c("Term","Assistant Professor","Associate Professor","Full Professor","Special Rank"))
## K-Means Clustering of Salary_Index Category
wss_vec <- NULL
set.seed(123)
for(i in 1:15){
  temp <- kmeans(all$Salary_Index, i, iter.max=25, nstart=1)
  wss_vec <- c(wss_vec, temp$tot.withinss)
}

wss_mat <- cbind(seq(1,15),wss_vec)

plot(wss_mat[,1],wss_mat[,2],pch=19,xlab='k number of clusters',ylab='Within-cluster Sum of Squares')
lines(wss_mat[,1],wss_mat[,2],type='l')

g_legend<-function(a.gplot){
  tmp <- ggplot_gtable(ggplot_build(a.gplot))
  leg <- which(sapply(tmp$grobs, function(x) x$name) == "guide-box")
  legend <- tmp$grobs[[leg]]
  return(legend)}

c <- ggplot(all2, aes(x=SI_Cat, fill=Subfield)) + geom_bar(position='dodge') + kyra_theme +
  scale_fill_grey() + xlab('SI Category') + ylab('Count') + 
  ggtitle('a) SI Category by Subfield') + theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle=45,hjust=1))


mylegend<-g_legend(c)

grid.arrange(a,b,mylegend,ncol=3)
